This paper deals with the age of information in a network, which is a metric commonly studied in the field of network information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization of transmission schemes, which is a topic relevant to control and optimization (cs.SI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper deals with the performance of a multicast network, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
